// ============================================================================
// STRICT GATE OVERLAY (TS 5.0+ JSONC comments are supported by tsc)
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Purpose: this file is an opt-in EXTENSION overlay for packages that have
//   completed their dead-code cleanup. It is NOT a wholesale flag flip on
//   tsconfig.base.json — flipping wholesale would surface 728 pre-existing
//   violations across packages/core (423) and packages/sdk (286) and break
//   CI on day-1.
//
// Flags added on top of tsconfig.base.json:
//   noUnusedLocals           — gate for unused locals (e.g. the prior
//                              `getAdaptiveEpsilon()` orphan in
//                              topologyRouter.ts that survived unnoticed
//                              because the gate was off)
//   noUnusedParameters       — gate for unused function parameters
//   noImplicitReturns        — gate for functions that may fall off
//                              without returning a value
//   noFallthroughCasesInSwitch
//                            — gate for switch cases that fall through
//                              without explicit break/return
//
// DO NOT OVERRIDE the following inherited keys here — they are
// base-contractual invariants and must come exclusively from
// tsconfig.base.json: target, module, moduleResolution, lib, strict,
// esModuleInterop, skipLibCheck, resolveJsonModule, declaration,
// declarationMap, noEmit. (Per code-reviewer-minimax-m3 round, `strict`,
// `esModuleInterop`, and `noEmit` were added because future contributors
// might naively copy-paste these here, which would no-op today but
// silently shadow the base if the base ever changed.)
//
// How to opt a package in (3-step recipe):
//   1. Bulk-fix all pre-existing TS6133/TS6196/etc. violations in the
//      package so that `npx tsc --noEmit -p packages/<pkg>/tsconfig.json`
//      returns 0 errors WHILE this overlay is also extended.
//   2. Switch the package's extends from `"../../tsconfig.base.json"`
//      to `["../../tsconfig.base.json", "../../tsconfig.strict.json"]`.
//   3. Verify CI green and any new commits must keep the gate clean
//      (no new TS6133/TS6196 errors from new code).
//
// Pilot: packages/plugin-sdk/tsconfig.json — was the first leaf package
//   with a clean baseline that already inlined the same 4 flags; it now
//   simply extends this overlay (inversion of the per-package duplication
//   pattern).
// ============================================================================
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "noUnusedLocals": true,
    "noUnusedParameters": true,
    "noImplicitReturns": true,
    "noFallthroughCasesInSwitch": true
  }
}
